cond weapon.  She reads the criteria, frowning slightly at the mention of Koda'Dal in the restrictions.. she is half of the hated race, though she hates that half deeply.  Reaching into her pack, she retrieves a quill, ink, and parchment, and in flowing Teir'Dal script (she has recently learned the language, a fact she is very proud of as she admires the Teir'Dal greatly) pens the following: <br>
<br>
&quot;My Ladies and Lords of the Scythe:<br>
I must say I am impressed by what I have heard about this hall.  I have read the policy concerning race and occupations.  I am half elven, half human, my elven side is Koda'Dal. I hope this would nt be detrimental to  me.  One other thing I am concerned about, is that I see nothing that indicates what is an appropriate minimum season for one interested in possibly joining this Guild.  As you may have noticed, I am very young yet, still only in my 6th season.  I am not even sure I am ready to join a guild yet.  But I am much interested in possibly applying here, when I am ready.  Could someone please contact me, or even leave a message here, I am more than willing to return to look for a response, so that my concerns may be addressed?<br>
<br>
Respectfully, <br>
Auryla (Thal'Kaarsh)<br>
Loyal servent of Innorukk<br>
Warrioress of His Hate <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silenaeonfirionavie>Silenae on FirionaVie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BoneMistress<br>
