<br>
Opening the door slowly, she was pleased to note the servant, wearing the livery of the Scythe, at her door, bearing in hand a message.  She took it and read it, smileing to herself.  Retrieving quill, ink, and parchment from her desk, she penned, in her flowing script:<br>
<br>
&quot;I am honored you woud choose to send a reply to me with such haste.  I am not surprised that my half elven blood would cause some to mistrust me, at first.  I am often mistaken for a LightBringer, much to my disdain.  As for the challenge of proving myself otherwise, I relish it.  Also, I would not expect gifts laid upon me. It is in me to work for what I have.  In the issue of my season, I would most likely wait until I have earned the right to sport my family name, before officially stepping forward to apply, officially, though I will do as you suggest, and look for those that wear your badge, as I would like to get to know those whom I may wish to someday join.  Again, I thank you for the quickness of the reply. <br>
Respectfully,<br>
Auryla (Thal'Kaarsh)<br>
Loyal Servant of Inorrukk<br>
Warrioress of His Hate&quot;<br>
<br>
Auryla tri-folded the note, and sealed it with a dollop of blood red wax, and imprinted her family crest into the wax.  Handing the note to the servant, she instructed &quot;Take this to whom it concerns, prmptly.&quot;<br>
<br>
The servant bowed, and quickly departed. Shutting the door behind him, Auryla finished her wine, and straped on her armor, and set out to Nektulos forest.  Halflings would do nicely to improve her skills,and her reputation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ssakaschaigidel>Ssakas Chaigidel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of the Scythe<br>
