<br>
Your heritage does not bother me, and you will see no extra distrust based upon your race, at least from me.  Many who walk the darker paths look upon my scales and recoil.  I know what it is to be hated by appearance alone, and I refuse to fall into that trap.  Not all with pale skin are of the Light, just as not all of us with scales are of the Empire.<br>
<br>
Let the Darkness protect you always.<br>
<br>
Jabbuk Ssakas Chaigidel<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ssakas laid the quill upon the desk, and looked with disgust upon the shakey script he had produced.  He prided himself both on his Teir'dal, and on his hand writing, and this letter appeared written by a first week student of the language.<br>
<br>
Another deep sigh overtook him.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Half elven warrior of Innorukk.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
His hand shot out at the decanter, rocketing it from the desk through the air until the wall halted its progress, the sound of crystal shattering filling the air, as the blood red wine covered the wall, running in streaks down towards the floor.  He looked down at his hand, quivering with the power of Hate, realizing that he had to learn to harness it, to control it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Use your hatred, Ssakas.&quot; Sarhea had told him.  &quot;Do not let it use you.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
